<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="344" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[140,1108,166,475]" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">
This Holarctic species is widely distributed in Europe, northern Asia, and throughout the 
<collectingCountry box="[227,378,307,333]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Parsons" box="[391,546,307,333]" firstAuthor="Parsons" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" pagination="121 - 278" refId="ref11921" refString="Parsons CT (1943) A revision of Nearctic Nitidulidae (Coleoptera). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 92: 121 - 278." type="journal article" year="1943">Parsons 1943</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Downie and Arnett" box="[557,845,307,334]" firstAuthor="Downie" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" refId="ref10845" refString="Downie NM, Arnett RH, Jr (1996) The beetles of northeastern North America. Sandhill Crane Press, Gainesville, 1721 pp." type="book" year="1996">Downie and Arnett 1996</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[895,981,307,333]" name="Canada" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">Canada</collectingCountry>
it has been recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[311,509,342,368]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
east to 
<collectingRegion box="[601,689,342,368]" country="Canada" name="Quebec" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">Québec</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[748,886,342,369]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="McNamara" box="[902,1102,343,369]" firstAuthor="McNamara" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" pagination="214 - 217" refId="ref11788" refString="McNamara J (1991) Family Nitidulidae: sap beetles. In: Bousquet Y (Ed) Checklist of Beetles of Canada and Alaska. Agriculture Canada Research Branch Publication 1861 / E.: 214 - 217." type="journal article" year="1991">McNamara 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Majka and Cline" box="[140,401,377,404]" firstAuthor="Majka" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" pagination="314 - 332" refId="ref11619" refString="Majka CG, Cline AR (2006) Th e Nitidulidae and Kateretidae (Coleoptera) of Nova Scotia and Prince Edward Island. Th e Canadian Entomologist 138: 314 - 332." type="journal article" year="2006">Majka and Cline 2006</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingRegion box="[453,590,378,404]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="7" pageNumber="344">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
it was found in a great variety of forested and open environments on flowers of trees and shrubs, in compost piles, and at sap (
<bibRefCitation author="Majka and Cline" firstAuthor="Majka" pageId="7" pageNumber="344" pagination="314 - 332" refId="ref11619" refString="Majka CG, Cline AR (2006) Th e Nitidulidae and Kateretidae (Coleoptera) of Nova Scotia and Prince Edward Island. Th e Canadian Entomologist 138: 314 - 332." type="journal article" year="2006">Majka and Cline 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
